1 (1) “Dangerous or deadly weapon” means a weapon, device, instrument,
2 material, or substance, whether animate or inanimate, that is used or readily
3 capable of being used to cause death or serious bodily injury, including an
4 explosive as defined in section 1603 of this title, except that “dangerous or
5 deadly weapon” does not include a pocket knife with a blade of less than 2.5
6 inches in length.
7 (2) “Firearm” has the same meaning as in subsection 4017(d) of this title.
8 (3) “State building” means a building or part of a building owned or
9 leased by the Department of Buildings and General Services where State
10 employees are regularly present for the purpose of performing their official
11 duties and includes all owned or leased State buildings, structures, and
12 appurtenances under the jurisdiction of the Commissioner of Buildings and
13 General Services except as provided in 29 V.S.A. § 152(a)(9) and 29 V.S.A.
14 chapter 5A.
15 (4) “State land” means all State-owned or State-leased land and grounds
16 under the jurisdiction of the Commissioner of Buildings and General Services
17 except as provided in 29 V.S.A. § 152(a)(9) and 29 V.S.A. chapter 5A.
18 Sec. 2. EFFECTIVE DATE
19 This act shall take effect on July 1, 2026.
